summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeVeganNourish and hydrate your lips while enhancing your pout's natural glow with e.l.f. Cosmetics' addicting Glow Reviver Lip Oil. The non-sticky formula imbues your pout with a sheer tint of color and glass-like shine while boosting your lips' natural hue.
details: DetailsBenefitsUltra-glossy tinted lip oil nourishes, hydrates & enhances your lips' natural colorNon-sticky, hydrating lip oil with a high-gloss finish & sheer wash of colorPlush, oversized cushion applicator for an even swipeInfused with lip-loving ingredients to nourish your poutCan be worn on its own or over lipsticke.l.f. is double-certified cruelty-free by Leaping Bunny & PETAe.l.f. is proud to partner with Fair Trade USA & manufacture products in Fair Trade Certified facilities; look for the Fair Trade Certified seal on your e.l.f. productFormulated WithoutPhthalatesParabensNonylphenol ethoxylatesTriclosanTriclocarbanHydroquinoneItem 2615649How To UseWear alone or as a top coat for an ultra-glossy finish.IngredientsPink Quartz: Hydrogenated Polyisobutene, Tridecyl Trimellitate, Polyisobutene, Phytosteryl/Octyldodecyl Lauroyl Glutamate, Hydrogenated Styrene/Isoprene Copolymer, Squalane, Prunus Armeniaca (Apricot) Kernel Oil, Persea Gratissima (Avocado) Oil, Simmondsia Chinensis (Jojoba) Seed Oil, Punica Granatum Seed Oil, Tocopheryl Acetate, Fragrance (Parfum), Diethylhexyl Syringylidenemalonate, Phenoxyethanol, Caprylyl Glycol, Caprylic/Capric Triglyceride, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-di-t-butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate, Tocopherol. May Contain: Red 6 Lake (CI 15850), Red 7 Lake (CI 15850), Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77499).Ingredients may change or vary from time to time. Please refer to the packaging of the product you received for the list of ingredients in your particular product.
how_to_use: Wear alone or as a top coat for an ultra-glossy finish.

reviews.headline: Nice color, but it caused lip irritation
reviews.comments: They should advertise this as plumping or having menthol. It has a really minty smell and a slight tingle when you put it on. My lips don't like menthol, but the ingredients didn't list it so I kept wearing it for about a week because I loved how it looked and felt. But by the end of the week my lips were so sore and sensitive. They went back to normal almost immediately after I stopped wearing the lip oil. If it didn't have whatever is causing the mintiness, I would definitely buy it again. They should really advertise it as plumping.

[I received this product in exchange for my honest review]

My wife loves this lip oil. It's so hydrating and makes her lips feel so soft, and the best part is it's not sticky at all. It gives a really nice glossy look with just a hint of color. Plus, the applicator is so big and fluffy, which she says is just satisfying to use.

reviews.headline: Loveeee
reviews.comments: This is so good! I have pink quartz, jam session, and the glitter on in super neutral. The lip oil feels so buttery and smooth on my lips and it is very glossy. It's also a really good consistency, not too thick like a gloss, but not too runny either. The one thing that could be improved is the packaging. The tube tends to leak a lot, but my glitter one doesn't for some reason. Overall, great formula, but maybe put it in a plastic bag when you travel.

reviews.headline: My new favorite gloss
reviews.comments: I love the giant applicator and how long it lasts. My only complaint is that it is slightly sticky.

reviews.headline: Weird Residue
reviews.comments: I had high hopes when I bought this product knowing Elf and it's amazing products, but when I put it on and it sat for a bit it left a weird Residue on the corners of my lips and i was shocked to say the least. I don't know if this happens to anyone else but when I tried it again and again it kept happening so I eventually just had to stop using it which made me kinda sad. But this might not happen to everyone and if you disagree with my rating I get to can totally see why someone would like this product.

reviews.headline: Everlasting Glow
reviews.comments: I recently purchased E.L.F. Cosmetics's Glow Reviver Lip Oil in Pink Quartz. This oil has the same shine as lip gloss, but the glow stays on all day long. Easy to use with the applicator wand, and keeps your lips hydrated with a pink tint that's perfect to keep your lips light with its pigmentation.  Love the shade and would buy it more colors.

faceoff_positive.comments: I love the Glow Reviver lip oil so much. I got it in Pink Quartz and it's so hydrating and the Pink Quartz shade gives you a very light pink tint. It's not sticky at all and for me it stays on for quite awhile. The oversized doe foot applicator is great at applying the lip oil. You can wear it over lipstick, but I really just love it on its own. I also love the slight mint scent as well, just makes it feel really fresh. Very happy with this lip oil!
faceoff_positive.headline: Great Lip Oil!

faceoff_negative.comments: I bought this product in the shade Coral Fixation, and I own other lips oils such as Dior, and this product is "drugstore" but wasn't as buttery and not to mention the applicator is peeling the small bristles are falling off into the product and the applicator is literally balding. I love elf products my entire makeup routine is E.L.F.  And i stand by their products but I was genuinely disappointed with this one
